	"description": "JavaScript is synchronous. This means that it will execute your code block by\norder after hoisting\n[https://scotch.io/tutorials/understanding-hoisting-in-javascript]. Before the\ncode executes, var and function declarations are “hoisted” to the top of their\nscope.\n\nThis is an example of a synchronous code:\n\nconsole.log(&#x27;1&#x27;)\n\nconsole.log(&#x27;2&#x27;)\n\nconsole.log(&#x27;3&#x27;)\n\nThis code will reliably log “1 2 3&quot;.\n\nAsynchronous requests will wait for a timer to finish or a request to respond\nwhile the rest of the ",
